cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the security and privacy of data stored in cloud servers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of blockchain technology and smart contracts suggests a distributed computing aspect, which could also place it in the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or databases (cs.DB). The use of state channels suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the implementation and evaluation of a prototype suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
